	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Easiest thing to do here is to have someone who can go into port (i.e. enchanter with evil-race illusion, or someone who is of an evil race).  Hand Tektite two carnelians and get the item in return.  Get a port to Lavastorm and go to Sol Temple and find Lord Lylfyx (sp?) of Burwood, give him the tektite and a peridot and he will give you the last wurm scale you need.  Nice thing about this, is that the scale can be traded.  After you kill Azdalin (PH is Gullerback - near 100% MR 47-51 summoning monkey) and Gylton (PH is Entalon, just a wussy wurm) and get their scales.  Turn them in to Fuzzmin in FV and get your wurmslayer.  I've done the wurmslayer quest 3 times now for my friends and guildmates.  The hardest part of it all is finding Fuzzmin alive.  Fuzzmin will not depop when you complete the quest like many boneheaded NPC's.
				</font>
			</td>

